---
// biome-ignore lint/correctness/noUnusedImports: used in Astro template
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="CLI Reference"
  description="Reference for all clip CLI commands — generate, install, auth, and test."
>
  <div class="docs-prose">
    <p class="lead">
      Reference for all clip commands. Each command includes its usage,
      options, and examples.
    </p>

    <h2 id="generate">clip generate</h2>
    <p>Parse a <code>clip.yaml</code> schema and generate a complete CLI project.</p>
    <pre><code>clip generate [--schema &lt;path&gt;] [--output &lt;dir&gt;]</code></pre>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>Default</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--schema &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
            <td><code>./clip.yaml</code></td>
            <td>Path to the schema file</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--output &lt;dir&gt;</code></td>
            <td><code>.clip-output/&lt;alias&gt;/</code></td>
            <td>Output directory for the generated project</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <h3>Example</h3>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip generate
✓ Parsed clip.yaml (5 endpoints)
✓ Generated CLI "todo" in .clip-output/todo/

$ clip generate --schema api.yaml --output ./my-cli
✓ Parsed api.yaml (3 endpoints)
✓ Generated CLI "myapp" in ./my-cli/`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      The generated project includes a Commander.js-based CLI with argument
      parsing, an HTTP client with auth injection, and TypeScript types.
    </p>

    <h2 id="install">clip install</h2>
    <p>Generate the CLI and install it globally via <code>bun link</code>.</p>
    <pre><code>clip install [--schema &lt;path&gt;]</code></pre>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>Default</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--schema &lt;path&gt;</code></td>
            <td><code>./clip.yaml</code></td>
            <td>Path to the schema file</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <h3>Example</h3>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip install
✓ Parsed clip.yaml (5 endpoints)
✓ Generated CLI "todo" in .clip-output/todo/
✓ Installed "todo" command globally`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      After installation, the generated CLI is available as a global command.
      Run <code>todo --help</code> to see available commands.
    </p>

    <h2 id="test">clip test</h2>
    <p>Run auto-generated tests against a live API to validate response shapes.</p>
    <pre><code>clip test &lt;alias&gt;</code></pre>
    <h3>Example</h3>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip test todo
✓ GET /todos — 200, shape valid
✓ POST /todos — 201, shape valid
✓ GET /todos/:id — 200, shape valid
✓ PATCH /todos/:id — 200, shape valid
✓ DELETE /todos/:id — 200, shape valid
5/5 tests passed`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      Tests are generated from the <code>response</code> schema defined for each
      endpoint. Each test validates that the API returns the expected HTTP status
      and that the response body matches the defined shape.
    </p>

    <h2 id="auth-set">clip auth set</h2>
    <p>Store API credentials for a generated CLI.</p>
    <pre><code>clip auth set &lt;alias&gt; [--key &lt;value&gt;] [--header &lt;name&gt;]</code></pre>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Option</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--key &lt;value&gt;</code></td>
            <td>API key value. If omitted, prompts interactively with hidden input.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>--header &lt;name&gt;</code></td>
            <td>Header name override. If omitted, reads from <code>clip.yaml</code>.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <h3>Example</h3>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip auth set todo --key "sk-abc123"
✓ Credentials saved for "todo"

$ clip auth set todo
Enter API key: ••••••••
✓ Credentials saved for "todo"`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      Credentials are stored in <code>~/.clip/&lt;alias&gt;/credentials.json</code>
      with restricted permissions (<code>0600</code>). The credential value is
      never logged to stdout or stderr.
    </p>

    <h2 id="auth-show">clip auth show</h2>
    <p>Display stored credentials for an alias (values are masked).</p>
    <pre><code>clip auth show &lt;alias&gt;</code></pre>
    <h3>Example</h3>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip auth show todo
Alias:  todo
Header: X-API-Key
Value:  sk-ab****23
Path:   ~/.clip/todo/credentials.json`}</code></pre>

    <h2 id="auth-remove">clip auth remove</h2>
    <p>Delete stored credentials for an alias.</p>
    <pre><code>clip auth remove &lt;alias&gt;</code></pre>
    <h3>Example</h3>
    <pre><code>{`$ clip auth remove todo
Remove credentials for "todo"? (y/N) y
✓ Credentials removed for "todo"`}</code></pre>
    <p>
      Prompts for confirmation before deleting. Removes the entire credential
      directory for the alias.
    </p>

    <h2 id="env">Environment Variables</h2>
    <div class="table-wrapper">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Variable</th>
            <th>Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><code>CLIP_HOME</code></td>
            <td>Override credential storage directory (default: <code>~/.clip</code>)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><code>CLIP_BASE_URL</code></td>
            <td>Override the <code>baseUrl</code> from <code>clip.yaml</code> at runtime</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>

<style>
  .docs-prose {
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .docs-prose .lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .docs-prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .docs-prose h2:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .docs-prose h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .docs-prose p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .docs-prose pre {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .table-wrapper {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  th {
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  td {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  td code {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }
</style>
